# Grandfathering UI Source Of Truth

For the grandfathering page, keep each UI area tied to one clear data source.

- The left organization list should render only the organizations that are in the visible prepared list for that page.
- Do not rebuild the left list from multiple fallback arrays when the page already has a visible list source.
- Clicking a row should store one normalized selected organization record, and the right-side detail should read from that selected record.
- Do not let the detail panel fall back to another organization just because that other record has richer data.
- If the selected organization is missing apps or other fields, show an empty or partial state for that same organization instead of switching records.
- Keep counts, row labels, selection state, and manual mapping rows aligned with the same normalized selected/list data.
